                <p>
                    Ear infections (otitis media) occur when fluid and pus build up in the middle ear, behind the eardrum, causing ear pain. This is often due to a cold or allergies. Ear infections are more common in children than adults. Most resolve without antibiotics and are treated with pain relievers and decongestants. A persistent ear infection may require antibiotics, and ear tubes may be needed for chronic infections.

                </p>  

